description:
&lt;p&gt;Wrightington, Wigan &amp; Leigh Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust would like to offer you the opportunity to join our Critical Care Team. The Unit is a combined 7 bedded Intensive Care and 4 bedded High Dependency Unit which flex beds depending on capacity and need.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Band 5 staff nurse who has a desire to work and develop their skills within Critical Care. For those post holders who do not already have a recognised Critical Care qualification they will be supported to complete a Critical Care induction and development package supported by the Unit’s Practice Educator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to do night duty and day duty on an internal rotation basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require you to work across all areas in the Trust which includes those that are designated as positive, asymptomatic and negative Covid wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidates will be required to present original certificates for qualifications at interview stage. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note interviews for this vacancy are planned to take place on the 17th of November and via Microsoft Teams&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any further details please contact Janet Enston, Practice Educator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel 01942822288/2380&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email : janet.enston@wwl.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
